      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Is Plan-Then-Act?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Plan-Then-Act is an agent architecture pattern where the entire action sequence is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "committed upfront before any tool call is made"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The planner produces a complete, fixed step list; the executor runs those steps in order without revisiting the plan. This contrasts with Plan-and-Execute (which re-plans after each step) and ReAct (which interleaves reasoning and action at every step)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Plan-Then-Act: plan phase produces a committed step list; act phase executes each step in order without revision",
          "title": "Plan-Then-Act commits the full plan upfront; no re-planning occurs during execution"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Plan-Then-Act is the right choice when the task structure is predictable and you want the LLM's planning effort concentrated in a single high-quality reasoning pass \u2014 not spread across multiple mid-execution calls."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Core Pattern"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The planner is instructed to produce a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "complete and final"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " plan. The prompt explicitly states that no revisions will occur during execution, which nudges the model to reason more carefully about ordering, dependencies, and tool availability upfront:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass ActionStep:\n    index: int\n    tool: str          # e.g. \"web_search\", \"run_code\", \"write_file\"\n    args: dict         # tool-specific arguments\n    rationale: str     # why this step is needed (from planner)\n    result: Optional[str] = None\n\nPLAN_THEN_ACT_PROMPT = \"\"\"\nYou are a planning agent. Given a goal, produce a COMPLETE, FINAL plan\nas a list of tool calls. The plan will be executed exactly as written \u2014\nno revisions will occur during execution.\n\nAvailable tools: {tools}\n\nGoal: {goal}\n\nReturn JSON:\n{{\"steps\": [\n  {{\"index\": 1, \"tool\": \"<tool_name>\",\n    \"args\": {{...}}, \"rationale\": \"<why>\"}},\n  ...\n]}}\n\nRules:\n- Every step must be executable with the tools listed above.\n- Assume each step succeeds. Do not add conditional branches.\n- Steps that depend on previous results may reference them as {{step_N_result}}.\n- Maximum 8 steps.\n\"\"\"\n\ndef plan(goal: str, available_tools: list[str]) -> list[ActionStep]:\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": PLAN_THEN_ACT_PROMPT.format(\n            goal=goal,\n            tools=\", \".join(available_tools),\n        )}],\n    )\n    data = json.loads(response.content[0].text)\n    return [ActionStep(**s) for s in data[\"steps\"]]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "{step_N_result}"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " placeholder syntax lets later steps reference the outputs of earlier ones without requiring a re-plan. The executor resolves these at runtime by string substitution before dispatching the tool call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Executing the Committed Plan"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Execution iterates through the step list once, passing prior results forward via the placeholder mechanism. The loop has no branching \u2014 every step runs unconditionally:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def execute_step(step: ActionStep, prior_results: dict[int, str]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Run one ActionStep, interpolating {{step_N_result}} placeholders.\"\"\"\n    # Replace placeholders with actual prior results\n    args_str = json.dumps(step.args)\n    for idx, result in prior_results.items():\n        placeholder = f\"{{step_{idx}_result}}\"\n        args_str = args_str.replace(placeholder, result[:1000])\n    args = json.loads(args_str)\n\n    # Dispatch to the correct tool\n    if step.tool == \"web_search\":\n        return web_search(args[\"query\"])\n    elif step.tool == \"run_code\":\n        return run_code(args[\"code\"])\n    elif step.tool == \"write_file\":\n        write_file(args[\"path\"], args[\"content\"])\n        return f\"Wrote {args['path']}\"\n    elif step.tool == \"send_email\":\n        send_email(args[\"to\"], args[\"subject\"], args[\"body\"])\n        return \"Email sent\"\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown tool: {step.tool}\")\n\ndef run_plan_then_act(goal: str, available_tools: list[str]) -> dict[int, str]:\n    \"\"\"Produce a plan then execute it completely.\"\"\"\n    steps = plan(goal, available_tools)\n    print(f\"Plan ({len(steps)} steps):\")\n    for s in steps:\n        print(f\"  {s.index}. [{s.tool}] {s.rationale}\")\n\n    results: dict[int, str] = {}\n    for step in steps:\n        print(f\"Executing step {step.index}...\")\n        results[step.index] = execute_step(step, results)\n        step.result = results[step.index]\n    return results"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This simplicity is the pattern's main advantage: execution is deterministic and fast. There are no mid-loop LLM calls \u2014 only tool calls \u2014 so latency is bounded by the slowest individual tool, not by a chain of LLM calls."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pre-Execution Plan Validation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Because the plan is never revised once execution starts, catching plan errors "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "before"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " execution is essential. A validation step uses the LLM to review the plan for logical issues \u2014 missing prerequisites, unreachable steps, wrong tool selection \u2014 and to return a corrected plan if needed:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "VALIDATE_PLAN_PROMPT = \"\"\"\nReview the following plan for a goal. Check:\n1. Are all steps executable with the given tools?\n2. Are there any missing prerequisite steps?\n3. Are there any steps that depend on information not yet available?\n4. Is the order correct?\n\nAvailable tools: {tools}\nGoal: {goal}\n\nPlan:\n{plan_text}\n\nReturn JSON:\n{{\"valid\": true | false,\n  \"issues\": [\"<issue 1>\", ...],  <- empty if valid\n  \"revised_steps\": [...]         <- only if valid=false; full corrected plan\n}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef validate_and_fix_plan(\n    steps: list[ActionStep],\n    goal: str,\n    available_tools: list[str],\n) -> list[ActionStep]:\n    plan_text = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"{s.index}. [{s.tool}] {s.rationale}\" for s in steps\n    )\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": VALIDATE_PLAN_PROMPT.format(\n            tools=\", \".join(available_tools),\n            goal=goal,\n            plan_text=plan_text,\n        )}],\n    )\n    result = json.loads(response.content[0].text)\n    if result[\"valid\"]:\n        return steps\n    print(f\"Plan invalid. Issues: {result['issues']}\")\n    return [ActionStep(**s) for s in result[\"revised_steps\"]]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Full Loop with Validation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Combining planning, validation, and execution into a single function:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def run_plan_then_act_with_validation(\n    goal: str,\n    available_tools: list[str],\n    max_retries: int = 2,\n) -> dict[int, str]:\n    \"\"\"Plan-Then-Act with pre-execution plan validation.\"\"\"\n    steps = plan(goal, available_tools)\n\n    for attempt in range(max_retries):\n        steps = validate_and_fix_plan(steps, goal, available_tools)\n        if all(s.tool in available_tools for s in steps):\n            break\n        print(f\"Retry {attempt + 1}: plan still references unavailable tools\")\n    else:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"Could not produce a valid plan after retries\")\n\n    print(f\"Validated plan ({len(steps)} steps). Executing...\")\n    results: dict[int, str] = {}\n    for step in steps:\n        results[step.index] = execute_step(step, results)\n    return results\n\n# Usage:\n# results = run_plan_then_act_with_validation(\n#     goal=\"Search for Python async libraries and write a comparison to report.md\",\n#     available_tools=[\"web_search\", \"run_code\", \"write_file\"],\n# )"
          }
        ]
      },
